# Minimum Requirements (MVP)

This document defines the **minimum expected functionality** for the XYZ Bank project.
If all items pass, the project meets baseline completion standards.

---

## 1) Core User Flows

### Customer Setup
- [ ] User can create a customer with a **name** and a **4-digit PIN**
- [ ] System generates and displays a **customer ID**
- [ ] Invalid PIN formats are rejected with a clear message

### Accounts
- [ ] User can open a **Checking** account
- [ ] User can open a **Savings** account
- [ ] New accounts start with a **0.00** balance
- [ ] Each account has a unique **account number**

---

## 2) Banking Operations

### Deposit
- [ ] Deposits must be **> 0**
- [ ] Balance updates correctly after deposit
- [ ] A deposit creates a **Transaction** record

### Withdraw
- [ ] Withdrawals must be **> 0**
- [ ] Withdrawals must not exceed balance (**no overdrafts**)
- [ ] Balance updates correctly after withdrawal
- [ ] A successful withdrawal creates a **Transaction** record
- [ ] A failed withdrawal does **not** create a transaction

### Transfer
- [ ] Transfers must be **> 0**
- [ ] Transfers must not exceed source balance
- [ ] Transfers update both accounts correctly
- [ ] Transfers are recorded (either in both accounts or a shared log)

---

## 3) Transaction History / Audit Trail
- [ ] User can view recent transactions for an account
- [ ] Each transaction shows at minimum:
  - [ ] type (deposit/withdraw/transfer)
  - [ ] amount
  - [ ] timestamp (or sequence number if you prefer)

---

## 4) Input Validation & UX
- [ ] Menu handles invalid choices without crashing
- [ ] Amount inputs reject non-numeric or invalid values gracefully
- [ ] Program does not terminate unexpectedly during normal use

---

## 5) Code Quality (Baseline)
- [ ] Uses **classes** for Customer and Accounts (not everything in main)
- [ ] Fields are **private** with getters/setters as appropriate
- [ ] Business logic is centralized (e.g., `BankService`)
- [ ] Source files are organized and named clearly
